title: load pretrained inception model failure
body_html:
configuration:
pytorch 0.3.1
python 3.6

I am trying to load a pretrained inception network

code:

inception = models.inception_v3(pretrained=True, num_classes=800, aux_logits=False)

error:

File "/opt/conda/envs/pytorch-py3.6/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torchvision/models/inception.py", line 27, in inception_v3
model.load_state_dict(model_zoo.load_url(model_urls['inception_v3_google']))
File "/opt/conda/envs/pytorch-py3.6/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torch/utils/model_zoo.py", line 66, in load_url
return torch.load(cached_file, map_location=map_location)
File "/opt/conda/envs/pytorch-py3.6/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torch/serialization.py", line 303, in load
return _load(f, map_location, pickle_module)
File "/opt/conda/envs/pytorch-py3.6/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torch/serialization.py", line 469, in _load
result = unpickler.load()
File "/opt/conda/envs/pytorch-py3.6/lib/python3.6/site-packages/torch/autograd/variable.py", line 77, in setstate
self.requires_grad, _, self._backward_hooks = state
ValueError: too many values to unpack (expected 3)

>     model.load_state_dict(model_zoo.load_url(model_urls['inception_v3_google']))
